ecial situations at banc of america securities llc where he was a salesman in the high yield group and traded distressed public securities before banc of america mr peskind was high yield sales manager at painewebber prior to paine webber he was a high yield salesman at morgan stanley from  to  mr peskind began his career at harvard management where he was an equity analyst and also a fixed income analyst mr peskind earned his ba degree in finance from the university of illinois in  and an mba in finance from the university of wisconsin in  michael donoghue president mr donoghue joined phoenix in april  as managing director and president of the firm mr donoghue has over  years of experience in the high yield and distressed corporate credit markets and serves on the investment committee at phoenix on a day to day basis he manages phoenixs business development and investor relations activities prior to joining phoenix mr donoghue worked for  years at morgan stanley  co where he was named a managing director in  he was morgans top producing salesman in their high yield bond business for many years he managed the high yield sales team and coordinated the syndication of financings for over  high yield companies subsequently he managed the distribution business for all corporate credit including high yield distressed debt bank loan trading and investment grade bonds mr donoghue served on morgans global fixed income management committee he earned a ba in economics from dartmouth college and an mba from harvard business school robert youree cfa chief financial officer mr youree joined phoenix in march  as chief financial officer and oversees the firms finance operations and compliance prior to phoenix mr youree cofounded and was president of silver leaf partners llc a brokerdealer originally focused on trade execution capital introduction and prime brokerage services prior to silver leaf mr youree was chief operating officer of orbitex management and orbitex hedge fund advisors where he coordinated operations of a  billion mutual fund complex and  million longshort equity hedge fund he has also served as director of research for fairfax capital management and as a trader and equity analyst for sage management in washington dc mr youree holds the cfa designation and received his ba from the university of virginia investment timothy bepler cfa senior research analyst coportfolio manager mr bepler joined phoenix in january  as senior vice president of risk management as part of the investment team mr bepler serves as the firms risk manager monitoring market risk and overseeing the portfolio hedges on a daily basis tim has over  years of experience on wall street as a portfolio manageranalyst prior to joining phoenix from  to  mr bepler was president of kinsale capital where he managed longshort portfolios and provided hedge funds with investment research and scenario hedging analysis from  to  mr bepler worked with orbitex management where he was the portfolio manager for a mm healthcare portfolio he was a senior healthcare analyst for merrill lynch from  to  and for credit suisse swiss american securities from  to  mr bepler holds the cfa designation and has an mba in finance from new york university dixon yee portfolio manager trader mr yee joined phoenix in july  as a trader and senior research analyst he is responsible for daytoday management of the firms lower volatility product working in conjunction with the firms fundamental credit analysts mr yee has over  years of experience on wall street prior to joining phoenix from  to  he was a portfolio manager for the credit opportunities fund at basso capital management from  to  mr yee was a director at banc of america securities where he managed proprietary capital for the white ridge unit and traded high yield bonds for the dealer desk mr yee worked at credit suisse first boston from  to  as a director in research covering the retail supermarket and textile sectors from  to  he was a vice president of research at chase securities and from  to  he was a vice president at oppenheimer  co mr yee holds an mba from dartmouth college as well as a bs in economics from the university of pennsylvania robert konefal director of research mr konefal joined phoenix in august  he currently heads the research team in addition to covering gaming media finance and travel prior to joining phoenix he was cohead of research and an analyst covering media and telecom companies at imperial capital a distressed debt brokerage firm prior to imperial he was the managing director in charge of global telecom media and technology ratings across high grade and high yield at moodys investors service the rating agency prior to moodys he was a lending officer at the bank of new york first in their loan workout group and then in their media and telecom levered loan originations group mr konefal received his mba from new york university and his ab from princeton university stefan lingmerth senior research analyst coportfolio manager mr lingmerth joined phoenix in may  as a senior research analyst as a part of the investment team he covers the home builders paper and forest products food  agriculture rental services and building product sectors prior to working at phoenix mr lingmerth worked at eidesis capital in new york from  to  where he covered companies in the health care homebuilding cable television and paper and forest products sectors mr lingmerth received a ba from halmstad university in sweden and also a ba from lincolnshire  humberside university in the united kingdom alex duncan cfa senior research analyst mr duncan joined phoenix in december  as a senior research analyst prior to that from  to  mr duncan was a managing director at parfour investment management focusing on long and short principal investments across the high yield leveraged loan and distressed markets mr duncan covered the chemicals healthcare building products cable media theaters and metals and mining sectors mr duncan’s responsibilities also included representation on bankruptcy court creditor committees and the negotiation of “workouts” and restructurings prior to parfour mr duncan was employed by citigroup alternative investments as a research analyst where his responsibilities included financial analysis due diligence and application of valuation methodology in the selection of principal investments in par stressed and distressed leveraged loans and high yield bonds prior to joining citigroup mr duncan was employed by metropolitan life insurance company as an analyst in the leveraged finance unit responsible for credit analysis of a variety of public and private financings and investments mr duncan is a cfa charterholder and is a member of the new york society of security analysts alternative investments committee mr duncan graduated with honors from drew university in  where he received a ba in economics mike beck cfa senior research analyst mr beck was previously a research analyst for seven years at goldentree asset management lp where he focused on identifying long and short investment opportunities in leveraged loans high yield and equity across a variety of sectors including retail consumer food grocery and entertainment from  to  mr beck was an assistant vice president at ge capital in the global media  communications group where he structured and executed over  billion in debt and equity investments prior to ge he was at fortis capital where he invested in loans mezzanine and salelease backs across the media  telecom shipping and offshore industries mr beck received a bs in finance cum laude from miami university oh and holds the cfa designation aloke agarwal senior research analyst mr agarwal joined phoenix in july  as a senior research analyst prior to working at phoenix mr agarwal was a director at nomura where he focused on identifying long and short investment opportunities in high yield distressed and leveraged loans across various sectors including paper chemicals aerospace and energy prior to his experience at nomura he worked in credit research at verition group llc and citadel investment group collectively from  to  where he recommended long and short investment opportunities in credit default swaps and convertibles in various sectors including financials homebuilders transportation and biotechnology mr agarwal received his bachelor of science in economics with concentrations in finance and insurance from the wharton school of the university of pennsylvania ivan kara senior research analyst mr kara joined phoenix in  as a senior research analyst prior to phoenix mr kara was a senior analyst at eventdriven funds zama capital advisers and p schoenfeld asset management collectively from  to   where he focused on identifying special situation equity and stresseddistressed credit investments prior to that mr kara spent six years at blackrock financial management where he led a team within special credit opportunities focusing on restructuring situations in both public and private markets prior to blackrock mr kara was a research analyst in the proprietary trading group at credit suisse focused on capital structure arbitrage and volatility strategies mr kara began his career in credit suisse’s asset finance investment banking group focused on capital raises for specialty finance companies as well as structuring esoteric assetbased financing transactions mr kara received an mba with distinction from columbia business school and ba with honors in economics from colgate university jackson logie research analyst mr logie joined phoenix as an analyst in august of  prior to phoenix mr logie worked as an investment banking analyst at imperial capital where he worked on a range of debt equity and mergers and acquisitions transactions across a variety of industries mr logie received a ba in economics from yale university business development and investor relations paul lucas director business development and investor relations mr lucas joined phoenix in november  as vice president of business development and investor relations he is responsible for developing new client relationships at the firm as well as maintaining existing ones prior to joining phoenix mr lucas spent four years at schultze asset management llc a distressed securities hedge fund manager that grew from approximately m to m during his tenure at schultze mr lucas was a vice president responsible for all aspects of business development and investor relations for the firms prospective and current clients he marketed the firms products globally to the entire spectrum of institutional hedge fund investors mr lucas holds a ba in finance from manhattanville college john mills senior vice president business development and investor relations mr mills joined phoenix in april of  as a senior vice president of marketing  investor relations prior to working at phoenix mr mills was director of marketing and investor relations for broadfin capital responsible for all aspects of marketing and client relations as the firm grew from m to bln before broadfin mr mills was the founding member of the marketing team at gsc group a bln credit manager in addition to other senior roles in the alternative investment management industry prior to this mr mills was a partner at sanford c bernstein  co responsible for the firms underwriting business executive vice president of nesbitt burns responsible for institutional equity research sales and trading in the us and director of equity research at bankers trust after eleven years in institutional equity sales at painewebber erin hubbard vice president business development and investor relations ms hubbard joined phoenix as senior associate of business development and investor relations in july  she is responsible for growing phoenixs client base as well as sustaining the firms current investor relationships prior to joining phoenix ms hubbard was a marketing and business development associate at ridgeway capital group llc at ridgeway she was responsible for marketing the firms various hedge funds and private equity funds to a wide range of investors ms hubbard holds an mba from new york universitys stern school of business and received her ba from the university of virginia andrew fair senior associate business development and investor relations mr fair joined phoenix in november  as an operations associate in  he joined the firm’s business development and investor relations department mr fair holds a ba in economics from loyola university maryland operations legal and compliance lance friedler general counsel and chief compliance officer mr friedler joined phoenix in june  as general counsel and chief compliance officer in this role he oversees the firm’s legal and compliance matters prior to joining phoenix mr friedler was a partner at sadis  goldberg where he counseled investment managers commodity pool operators and commodity trading advisors on structuring and forming us and nonus investment funds commodity pools and separately managed accounts mr friedler also prepared and negotiated various types of agreements including seed capital agreements and joint venture agreements mr friedler also regularly advised investment managers commodity pool operators and commodity trading advisors on registration and ongoing compliance issues with the sec cftc nfa and finra prior to joining sadis  goldberg mr friedler was a partner at mccarter  english where he represented numerous private investment funds and counseled investment advisers mr friedler holds a jd degree cum laude from new york law school and a bs from oneonta state college tyler defibaugh chief operations and risk officer mr defibaugh joined phoenix in october  as director of operations he oversees the firms portfolio and trading operations in addition to overseeing the firms technology infrastructure prior to joining phoenix mr defibaugh was chief operating officer of silver leaf partners llc where he managed the trading and operations of a brokerdealer that provides trade execution prime brokerage services and marketing services to the institutional community before silver leaf mr defibaugh was head trader at orbitex management llc and monument advisors llc mr defibaugh received his ba from shippensburg university robert beck vice president operations mr beck joined phoenix in july  as vice president of operations he manages all aspects of portfolio operations accounting and administration and assists in maintaining the firms compliance program prior to joining phoenix mr beck was vice president of operations for silver leaf partners llc a nasd brokerdealer focused on trade execution capital introduction and prime brokerage services to the hedge fund community prior to silver leaf mr beck held various operations positions for highbridge capital management llc and nebo management llc mr beck holds a bm from manhattan school of music susan bowen vice president client services ms bowen joined phoenix in april  she handles all aspects of client services including responding to investor inquiries producing investor reports and maintaining account information she also serves as the firms office manager maintains the firms human resources records and assists in the fund accounting process prior to joining phoenix ms bowen spent three years at schultze asset management llc where she was responsible for all aspects of client services prior to schultze ms bowen was the sales  marketing coordinator at ginsburg development companies llc  to  ms bowen holds a ba from manhattanville college jerry wong senior operations associate mr wong joined phoenix in july  as a senior operations associate prior to joining phoenix from  to  mr wong was the head of operations for eidesis capital llc where he was responsible for the middle and back office before eidesis mr wong was a vice president fixed income analyst at bear stearns asset management for six years prior to bsam mr wong was an assistant section head of the portfolio auditing department at bea associates mr wong received his bs in finance and economics cum laude from new york university ryan benincasa senior associate mr benincasa joined phoenix in february  as an operations associate his responsibilities include portfolio operations accounting and administration he also assists in client services including maintaining client documents and databases prior to phoenix mr benincasa worked in the operations and investor relations departments at tudor investment corporation mr benincasa holds a ba from the university of virginia where he played varsity lacrosse and was a member of the  ncaa national championship team patricia horton office manager and senior operations associate ms horton joined phoenix in october  as operations associate her responsibilities include general office management and administration as well as assisting all areas of the firm prior to joining phoenix ms horton was employed by michael page international where she was quickly promoted from office coordinator to human resources coordinator in  ms horton holds a ba from curry college   phoenix investment adviser llc privacy statement terms of use contact us phoenix investment adviser — phoenix investment adviser llc of new york city skip to content  skip to navigation personal tools search site advanced search… homeabout usour teamnews  publicationscontact us info phoenix investment adviser value investors in the us high yield market   phoenix investment adviser llc privacy statement terms of use contact us phoenix investment adviser llc of new york city skip to content  skip to navigation personal tools search site advanced search… homeabout usour teamnews  publicationscontact us contact form info deep value investors in the stressed bond market fill in this form to contact the site owners name please enter your full name email required please enter your email address subject required message required pl