 really on sale” —charles keenan «less vermont at age  brian pelkey was hired by ef hutton his first job was coldcalling prospective clients and offering municipal bonds with an more» vermont at age  brian pelkey was hired by ef hutton his first job was coldcalling prospective clients and offering municipal bonds with an  coupon a few years later during the crash of  he got a taste of wall street panic “i remember in disbelief watching that computer screen” he recalls it taught him that “when turmoil seems the greatest most times the best thing to do is nothing” that lesson is timely now as political news gives the jitters to some of his clients at morgan stanley wealth management’s office in colchester pelkey  taps proven managers to do his stockpicking among other things he favors global highquality dividend payers along with preferred securities with a fixed interest rate that eventually floats with the london interbank offered rate and he’s still a fan of munis given vermont’s plus state tax rate for the highest earners producing solid portfolios that generate a reasonable income stream he says gives clients the patience to sit through unsettling times —charles keenan «less virginia stephan cassaday took an interest in investing at age  when his father bought him  shares of airplane manufacturer cessna the stock doubled inmore» virginia stephan cassaday took an interest in investing at age  when his father bought him  shares of airplane manufacturer cessna the stock doubled in a year and cassaday took his  in profits and bought a drum set he still plays in his basement to let off steam pressure is nothing new he went independent in  going more than four years without a paycheck and borrowing from credit cards to meet payroll before going into the black now he counts  households as clients mainly civil servants in the washington area last summer cassady  went entirely with active managers “it’s a stockpicker’s market” he says “everyone loves indexes when everyone loves something it’s almost always the wrong thing to do” he sees value in health care and financials likewise “emerging markets are dirt cheap” as well as some european companies “if the eu blows up does that mean volkswagen is not going to sell bugattis and lamborghinis to the chinese or nestlé is not going to sell chocolate” he asks —charles keenan «less washington one of erik morgan’s clients with a net worth north of  million wasn’t getting much respect at a ferrari dealership his cargo shorts and zz topmore» washington one of erik morgan’s clients with a net worth north of  million wasn’t getting much respect at a ferrari dealership his cargo shorts and zz top beard might have been the problem so morgan  of seattle’s freestone capital management became his successful negotiator morgan’s willingness to tackle the unusual extends to the investments he puts in his clients’ portfolios recently they included a  million portfolio of trailer parks mainly in alabama michigan and ohio the starting rate of return was  but it could be boosted by higher occupancy and rent increases morgan says he looks for ways to provide returns that aren’t correlated to stocks lately that has included some master limited partnerships reits and businessdevelopment companies in equities international stocks offer better value than domestic shares he contends he’s bullish on asia but cautions that investors there must make a significant financial commitment and “be willing to endure the ups and downs” —charles keenan «less west virginia david miller  once worked as a bank auditor crisscrossing the state to evaluate corporate borrowers “you got to see what businesses were doingmore» west virginia david miller  once worked as a bank auditor crisscrossing the state to evaluate corporate borrowers “you got to see what businesses were doing well and what businesses were hurting” he says “i thought you could use the same philosophy to identify sectors where you could make money” miller was recruited in the early s by ferris baker watts which was bought by rbc today he favors financials health care energy materials and industrials he mainly invests in etfs tapping three sources for advice rbc dorsey wright and first trust all three must align for him to dive into a sector which typically shows value and momentum he favors domestic given bullishness over rising rates deregulation and repatriation of overseas corporate cash in fixed income he likes discounted floatingrate bonds such as mortgagebacked securities and senior loans in highquality companies “we have to fight against rising rates which lots of clients haven’t experienced” he says —charles keenan «less wisconsin andrew burish a ubs financial services advisor in madison joins clients to ride motorcycles in locales such as california mexico and europe butmore» wisconsin andrew burish a ubs financial services advisor in madison joins clients to ride motorcycles in locales such as california mexico and europe but when it comes to investing he’s less adventurous favoring good oldfashioned buyandholds he looks for dividend payers with sustained doubledigit returns on equity over the past  years and avoids value traps by emphasizing freecash flow “this means they can survive a storm” he says “clients who are waiting for a recovery market get paid handsomely while they wait” to that end he likes us financials which now make up  of his domestic equities he thinks they could double in five years thanks to projected corporatetax cuts rising interest rates and deregulation energy makes up another  burish  a longtime proponent of international stocks has had to preach patience in recent years as they’ve underperformed us shares but the strong dollar makes goods produced abroad cheaper for americans aiding foreign exporters —charles keenan «less wyoming jeffrey vincent started at lpl financial in  not long after the stock market crashed and oil bust “most everybody thought i was going to fail”more» wyoming jeffr